<tal:layout define="columns1 default">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xml:lang="en"
      lang="en"
      metal:use-macro="context/@@main_template/master"
      i18n:domain="launchpad"
>
  <body>
    <metal:heading fill-slot="pageheading">
      <h1>Launchpad FAQ</h1>
    </metal:heading>

<div metal:fill-slot="main">

    <dl class="faq">
        <dt>How can I get in touch with the Launchpad team?</dt>

            <dd>
            The Launchpadders can be found on IRC on
            <code>irc.freenode.net</code>, on the <code>#launchpad</code>
            channel. The <a href="https://lists.ubuntu.com/mailman/listinfo/launchpad-users">launchpad-users</a>
            mailing list is used for discussions.
            </dd>

        <dt>Where can I get the source code for Launchpad?</dt>

            <dd>
            Launchpad is currently not a free software/open source project.
            </dd>

        <dt>What are the copyright terms for contributing to Rosetta?</dt>

            <dd>
            See our <a href="/legal">legal details page</a>.
            </dd>

        <dt>How do I sign the Ubuntu Code of Conduct?</dt>

            <dd>
              You need to follow these steps, in order:

              <ol>
                <li>Go to <a href="https://launchpad.net/codeofconduct/1.0/"
                  >https://launchpad.net/codeofconduct/1.0/</a>
                </li>
                <li>Click on the "Download This Version" link and save it with
                  the name <em>ubuntu-coc.txt</em> in your home directory
                </li>
                <li>Open it with your favorite text editor and read it 
                  carefully
                </li>
                <li>Now, open a terminal and run the command 
                  <code>gpg --clearsign ~/ubuntu-coc.txt</code>.
                  (This will create a file named <em>ubuntu-coc.txt.asc</em>)
                </li>
                <li>Open the <em>ubuntu-coc.txt.asc</em> file with your favorite
                  text editor and copy all its contents
                </li>
                <li>Go to <a href="https://launchpad.net/codeofconduct/1.0/+sign"
                  >https://launchpad.net/codeofconduct/1.0/+sign</a>,
                  paste that file's contents in that page and submit it
                </li>
              </ol>

            </dd>
    </dl>

</div>

</body>
</html>
</tal:layout>
